President Obama expressed deep sadness over the passing of Sargent Shriver, describing him as one of the brightest lights of the greatest generation. Shriver's long and distinguished career made him a symbol of public service, and he is best known for founding the Peace Corps. The President acknowledged the impact of the Peace Corps on communities worldwide and the countless lives that have been improved through Shriver's efforts to address inequality and injustice. President Obama extended his thoughts and prayers to the Shriver family during this difficult time.